1. Core Requirements Analysis
Functional Requirements:
Process payments from multiple sources (credit/debit cards, wallets, bank transfers, cryptocurrencies, etc.).
Support recurring payments, one-time transactions, and refunds.
Provide real-time payment status updates.
Non-Functional Requirements:
High availability and fault tolerance.
Scalability to handle peak loads.
Security compliance (e.g., PCI DSS).
Low latency for better user experience.
Audit trails for accountability.
